# ELB & ASG Lab - Manual Instructions

## Overview
This lab builds a highly available web application infrastructure using an Application Load Balancer (ALB) and Auto Scaling Group (ASG). Traffic from the internet hits the ALB, which distributes it across EC2 instances managed by the ASG across two availability zones.

## Architecture Diagram
```
Internet
    |
[ALB - Port 80]
    |
[Target Group]
   / \
[EC2] [EC2]   <-- managed by ASG (min: 2, max: 4)
  AZ-1a      AZ-1b
```

## Prerequisites
- AWS Account with appropriate permissions
- AWS Console access

